tldr: The user wanted to add a "Surprise me" button that opens a random post.
  The button was implemented in the FilteredPosts component, using the existing
  Button component with a secondary variant, and navigates to a random post
  using the Next.js router.
overview: The user wanted to add a "Surprise me" button to the application that
  would open a random post. The agent began by examining the existing
  component, understanding how posts are structured and routed, and identifying
  the best location for the new button. After reviewing several files, the
   component was chosen as the ideal place. The implementation
  involved importing the  hook from , creating a
   function to select a random post and navigate to its slug,
  and finally adding the  component with the specified variant and
  positioning it at the top right of the  component.
